page.title: 01ERISWELL WARREN
page.content: Here is a whole block of cultivated land, half coniferous forest and half intensively farmed as part of the Elveden Estate. There are no public roads, access being only on a couple of bridle tracks, all other tracks are private and lead to farm complexes. For details of the forest section see 0580 0285 and for the farm refer to 0580 0276. The photographs for here show the 200 year old Scots pines which were stunted when young to try to form a hedge, and some of the recent planting which also acts as coverts for game birds such as pheasants.
